  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc2\u0dd3 \u0dc3\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dcf\u0d9a\u0dca\u0da7 \u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0db0\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dba \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0db1 \u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dd4",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Rishi Sunak gets the Prime Ministership",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to foreign media, Rishi Sunak, the former Finance Minister (Chancellor) of the country, will get the vacant post of British Prime Minister.",
        "The foreign media said that Rishi Sunak, the former Finance Minister (Chancellor) of the country, will get the vacant post of British Prime Minister.",
        "With the 42-year-old Sunak of Indian origin succeeding in the leadership battle of the ruling party 'Kovsavertiv'. The British Prime Minister is held by the leader of the ruling party. The current ruling party is the 'Conservative' party.",
        "A poll to select candidates for party leadership was held yesterday (18), where Rishi Sunak received the majority of the votes, the poll was held within the 'Conservative' party.",
        "There are 358 members of the Conservative Party in the British Parliament, and the candidate who wins the consent and trust of the largest group of members will be the leader of the Conservative Party and the British Prime Minister.",
        "Several polls will be held among the 'Conservative' party MPs regarding the selection of a suitable party leader. That leaves two candidates. When a poll was held yesterday (18), there were five candidates for the party leadership and the post of Prime Minister.",
        "The five are former Finance Minister Rishi Sunak, Foreign Affairs Minister Liz Truss, Minister of State for Trade Penny Mordaunt, MP Kemi Bednock and MP Tom Tugendart.",
        "In yesterday's (18) poll, former Finance Minister (Chancellor) Rishi Sunak received the support of 115 Conservative Party MPs. The number of MPs supported by State Minister for Trade Penny Mordont is 82.",
        "The number of people who supported Foreign Affairs Minister Liz Truss was 71. Member of Parliament Kemi Bednok received the support of 58 members and Tom Tugendat received the support of 31 members. Tom Tugendart, who received the support of the least number of MPs, withdrew from the party leadership battle. In the end, polls are held within the party until two candidates are left.",
        "Boris Johnson, who was in the position of Prime Minister, had to leave the party leadership as well as the position of Prime Minister due to opposition from the 'Conservative' party. The reason for the protest was Johnson, the violation of the Covid laws and the offer of a high government position to an MP who was accused of sex. Johnson will act as acting Prime Minister until a new party leader and Prime Minister is chosen."
      ],
